## Markdown authoring style

When you author or edit any `.md` / `.mdx` file in this repo (including
`docs/`, `labs/**/LAB.md` and `GLOSSARY.md`, `.cursor/agents/*.md`,
`.cursor/skills/**/SKILL.md`, `.cursor/commands/*.md`, project rules
themselves, and the root `README.md`), do not hard-wrap paragraphs at
72 / 80 / 100 chars. Wrap at ~240 chars or, preferred, write one
sentence per line ("semantic line breaks"). Tables, code fences, and
list items follow normal markdown rules. The goal is editable raw
markdown, not 1990s mailing-list width.